  ${
    $d k n A $.  $d k ph $.  $d k n F $.  $d k n Z $.  $d k M $.
    explecnv.1 $e |- Z = ( ZZ>= ` M ) $.
    explecnv.2 $e |- ( ph -> F e. V ) $.
    explecnv.3 $e |- ( ph -> M e. ZZ ) $.
    explecnv.5 $e |- ( ph -> A e. RR ) $.
    explecnv.4 $e |- ( ph -> ( abs ` A ) < 1 ) $.
    explecnv.6 $e |- ( ( ph /\ k e. Z ) -> ( F ` k ) e. CC ) $.
    explecnv.7 $e |- ( ( ph /\ k e. Z ) ->
                       ( abs ` ( F ` k ) ) <_ ( A ^ k ) ) $.
    $( A sequence of terms converges to zero when it is less than powers of a
       number ` A ` whose absolute value is smaller than 1.  (Revised by Mario
       Carneiro, 26-Apr-2014.) $)
